1)Out of range issue:

A)Function: IoHwAb_Init

Following module and Global variables are going out of range,

Module Variables:-
1. BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32,
2. Batt_Volt_M_f32,
3. SysCVSwitch_Volt_M_f32,
4. Temperature_Volt_M_f32

Global Variables:-
1. BattSwitched_Volt_f32,
2. Batt_Volt_f32,
3. SysCVSwitch_Volt_f32,
4. TemperatureADC_Volt_f32

Analysis:-

Global variables BattSwitched_Volt_f32, Batt_Volt_f32, SysCVSwitch_Volt_f32, TemperatureADC_Volt_f32 are updating at the SRC lines 597-600 as below,

Rte_IWrite_IoHwAb_Init_BattSwitched_Volt_f32(BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32);
Rte_IWrite_IoHwAb_Init_Batt_Volt_f32(Batt_Volt_M_f32);
Rte_IWrite_IoHwAb_Init_SysCVSwitch_Volt_f32(SysCVSwitch_Volt_M_f32);
Rte_IWrite_IoHwAb_Init_TemperatureADC_Volt_f32(Temperature_Volt_M_f32);

The module internal variables BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32, Batt_Volt_M_f32, SysCVSwitch_Volt_M_f32, Temperature_Volt_M_f32 are updating at SRC line 591-594 as below,

BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32 = ((float32)BattSwitchedADC_Cnt_T_u16) * D_ADCVOLTSPERCNT_ULS_F32 * k_VswitchScale_Uls_f32;
Batt_Volt_M_f32 = ((float32)BattADC_Cnt_T_u16) * D_ADCVOLTSPERCNT_ULS_F32 * k_VbattScale_Uls_f32;
SysCVSwitch_Volt_M_f32 = BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32;
Temperature_Volt_M_f32 = (((float32)TemperatureADC_Cnt_T_u16) * D_ADCVOLTSPERCNT_ULS_F32 * k_TempSensorScale_Uls_f32) + k_TempSensorOffset_Volt_f32;

The temporary variables BattSwitchedADC_Cnt_T_u16, BattADC_Cnt_T_u16, TemperatureADC_Cnt_T_u16 are updating at SRC lines 586-588 as below,

BattSwitchedADC_Cnt_T_u16 = DMAData_G_str.SlowADC_Cnt_u16[D_BATTSWITCHEDCHN_CNT_U16] & D_ADCRESULTMASK_CNT_U16;
BattADC_Cnt_T_u16 = DMAData_G_str.SlowADC_Cnt_u16[D_BATTCHN_CNT_U16] & D_ADCRESULTMASK_CNT_U16;
TemperatureADC_Cnt_T_u16 = DMAData_G_str.SlowADC_Cnt_u16[D_TEMPSNSRCHN_CNT_U16] & D_ADCRESULTMASK_CNT_U16;

hence the the module interanal variables are calculated at SRC line no 591-594 as below,

BattSwitched_Volt_M_f32 = 500(4095*0.0012210012210012*100).... Src line 591
Batt_Volt_M_f32=500 = 500(4095*0.0012210012210012*100).... Src line 592

which are out of range values.
